{"id":618437,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flag_of_Mozambique","text":"The flag of Mozambique was adopted on May 1, 1983.\nAppearance.\nIt has a horizontal tricolour of green, white-fimbriated black and yellow with the red isosceles triangle based on the hoist-side bearing the yellow five-pointed star that bears an AK-47 assault rifle with the bayonet attached to the barrel crossed by the hoe superimposed on an open book.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Mozambique","surface_form":"Mozambique","offset":12},{"uri":"Horizontal","surface_form":"horizontal","offset":72},{"uri":"Tricolour","surface_form":"tricolour","offset":83},{"uri":"Green","surface_form":"green","offset":96},{"uri":"White","surface_form":"white","offset":103},{"uri":"Fimbriation","surface_form":"fimbriated","offset":109},{"uri":"Black","surface_form":"black","offset":120},{"uri":"Yellow","surface_form":"yellow","offset":130},{"uri":"Red","surface_form":"red","offset":146},{"uri":"Isosceles_triangle","surface_form":"isosceles triangle","offset":150},{"uri":"Hoist_(flag)","surface_form":"hoist-side","offset":182},{"uri":"Star","surface_form":"star","offset":225},{"uri":"AK-47","surface_form":"AK-47 assault rifle","offset":244},{"uri":"Bayonet","surface_form":"bayonet","offset":273}]}